contents:
Per Curiam,
Notwithstanding the able and ingenious argument of learned counsel for appellant, we are not convinced that there is any error in that part of the learned trial judge’s ehai'ge recited in the assignment of error. On the contrary, we are all satisfied that his construction of the act, under which the tax in question was imposed, is strictly correct. There is nothing in the question involved that requires discussion.
Judgment affirmed.
